# Struxa CMS version (do not bump locally)

The values in **`src/CmsVersion.php`**, **`composer.json`** → `"version"`, **`README.md`** → `**Version:** …`, and **`storage/cms-updates.example.json`** → `cms.latest_version` / `title` / `summary` are the **installed Struxa CMS release**. They must **only** change when the user **updates Struxa** (installer, ZIP merge, or in-app update) and upstream ships a new number.

**Do not** increment these for FL350-only work (themes, plugins, Docker, local patches). The assistant must not treat “finished a task” as a reason to bump `1.0.52` → `1.0.53` etc.

When you ship **plugin or theme** changes, bump **`plugins/<slug>/plugin.json`** → `"version"` (semver) in the same commit instead. Do not bump Struxa’s four version files for that.

If the user explicitly asks to align version files with a **specific** Struxa release they are merging, set all four to **that** release’s version in the same commit as the merge.

The user may refer to this as “page number”; they mean **Struxa’s version number** from upstream, not an assistant-invented increment.
